comments: Maxey (PHI) reaches toward the ball when he makes clean contact with it to begin the dislodge before incidental contact occurs with Murray's (ATL) left arm on the driving shot attempt.
Murray (ATL) trails Maxey (PHI) with a bent forearm when marginal contact occurs on the driving shot attempt.
Maxey (PHI) retreats in Murray's (ATL) path when he grazes Murray's arm at the end of the drive, and the contact is marginal.

Maxey's (PHI) left hand slides off Murray's (ATL) side during his shooting motion, causing marginal contact to occur. Any lower-body contact is due to Murray's outward extended leg following his release.
Maxey (PHI) gathers the ball on his right foot and two steps before his jump shot attempt.
Murray (ATL) contests Maxey's (PHI) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) extends his hand and arm across the top of Johnson's (ATL) head during his driving shot attempt.
Young (ATL) avoids making contact with Maxey (PHI) during his jump shot attempt.
Maxey (PHI) is moving alongside Young's (ATL) path and the body contact that occurs as they come together during the drive is marginal.
Bey (ATL) avoids stepping out of bounds while still in possession of the ball.
Bey (ATL) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes three steps prior to releasing his pass.
ATL's request for a timeout is granted at the time of the request, before Murray (ATL) receives the ball.
Murray (ATL) releases the inbounds pass within five seconds.

Replay review of the foul called on Maxey (PHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Maxey is jumping from point A to point B to contest Young's (ATL) driving shot attempt when his right leg makes illegal contact to Young's body.
Young (ATL) makes contact with the ball, dislodging it from Maxey's (PHI) control before any follow-through contact to his wrist/hand.
The ball deflects off Maxey's (PHI) leg prior to it going out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to ATL.

Maxey (PHI) extends his upper body and moves laterally into Young's (ATL) path, initiating contact with Young's body that affects his SQBR. The contact occurred before Young gathered and should have been assessed as a non-shooting foul.
Beverley's (PHI) arms are extended slightly as he is firming up in Johnson's (ATL) path when marginal contact occurs during the off-ball screen.
Johnson (ATL) grabs Harris' (PHI) jersey before wrapping his arm around Harris' waist in the post, affecting his FOM.
Okongwu (ATL) brushes Harris' (PHI) off-arm during the drive, which he is able to move through.
Okongwu (ATL) releases his resting hands from Morris Sr.'s (PHI) back and does not apply force when he moves toward the long rebound.
Morris Sr. (PHI) does not maintain verticality when he lowers his arm and initiates contact to Johnson's (ATL) arm that affects his shot attempt near the basket.
Morris Sr. (PHI) retracts his extended arms as he slides them off Johnson (ATL) during the off-ball screen. The contact is marginal.
Johnson (ATL) removes his hand as it brushes Harris (PHI) at the start of his drive and aligns himself alongside Harris' path.
Okongwu (ATL) cleanly blocks Harris' (PHI) driving shot attempt before incidental contact occurs.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Murray's (ATL) arm during the release.
Morris Sr. (PHI) makes incidental contact with Okongwu (ATL) as both players attempt to establish a position to pursue the rebound.
Harris (PHI) turns his body as he jumps into Johnson (ATL), making arm and body contact that affects his shot attempt near the basket.
Oubre Jr.'s (PHI) shot initially makes contact with the rim before Okongwu (ATL) gets to the ball. Any contact that occurs thereafter is deemed incidental.
Morris Sr. (PHI) commits a take foul on Young (ATL).
Young (ATL) reaches in and makes slight contact with Beverley's (PHI) arm, which he is able to move through.
